{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T10:53:46.310Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Sequence Processing Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sequence processing"},{"type":"text","text":" in Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) is the capability to handle data where the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"order matters"},{"type":"text","text":" and elements are inherently related to previous or future elements. Unlike feedforward neural networks that process each input independently, RNNs use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"loops to pass information from one step to the next"},{"type":"text","text":", allowing them to process sequences of arbitrary length while retaining context."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"sequence"},{"type":"text","text":" is defined as an ordered list of objects, events, or data items."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Sequence Processing Matters in Generative AI"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sequence processing is fundamental to generative AI because most generative tasks involve creating ordered outputs:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Application"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Sequence Matters"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"tex