","text":"RNNs are specifically structured for processing sequential data and are predominantly employed in Natural Language Processing (NLP)."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Sequence Processing Works (Core Mechanics)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The key mechanism:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"RNNs use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"parameter sharing"},{"type":"text","text":" — the repeated application of the same set of parameters across all time steps. This makes RNNs efficient for sequences, as the same logic is reused regardless of sequence length."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"At each time step:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The network takes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"two inputs"},{"type":"text","text":":\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Current data point"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"x_t"}},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., word in sentence, temperature reading)\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hidden state from previous step"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"h_{t-1}"}},{"type":"text","text":" (memory summarizing past inputs)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"These are combined using weights and activation functions:"}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"h_t = f(W_{xh} \\cdot x_t + W_{hh} \\cdot h_{t-1} + b)"}},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"y_t = g(W_{hy} \\cdot h_t + c)"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where:\n- "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"h_t"}},{"type":"text","text":" = new hidden state (updated memory)\n- "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"y_t"}},{"type":"text","text":" = output at time step "},